post_text:
Hello,
This is Kylee McDonald, Chase High School and Raymond Junior High School principal. This is an update on the continuous learning plan that we began March 30th. The goal for the Continuous Learning Plan is to keep every student engaged and learning throughout the end of the school year. The work assigned to your student is not optional; grades are being recorded. Please keep in mind that your students' grades can increase, maintain, or decrease depending on their participation, engagement, and assignments being turned in. Please help your student understand the importance of finishing this year strong. All teachers and myself can be reached by email or phone with any questions or concerns. Thank you, We understand that this situation is not ideal and presents difficulties. Effort is what matters most. Thank you for all you're doing for our kiddos

post_text: School lunches will not be served on Good Friday, April 10 or Monday, April 13.

post_text:
Chase/Raymond School Family,

Our first day of "school" was encouraging! We had a high percentage of students log in and begin their classes and our continuous learning activities. I know that we had a few glitches, internet connection issues, etc. But we will continue to work through those and things will get smoother.

We were unable to obtain a direct internet connection to the Raymond gym. We are working through other options (individual hotspots) and other possible solutions.

Tomorrow lunches will be served from 11:00 AM - 12:30 PM. Thanks to our Food Service crew for their hard work! We also thank our custodial staff for the constant cleaning and for helping to keep us all safe.

Have a great evening and I will update you again soon!

Jim Johnson

post_text: Unfortunately, we will not be able to get an internet connection at the Raymond gym. Our building admin and teachers will work with our Raymond students on using downloadable jump drives and other options.

post_text:
Chase/Raymond School Family,

Thank you for the smooth distribution of belongings and instructional materials today. We saw all but a few of you and arrangements will be made with those that couldn’t make it today.

Our continuous learning activities will begin tomorrow. There will inevitably be a few glitches and frustrations. I ask for your patience while we work through those issues. Stay in contact with your teachers and just do what you can do. It will be OK.

MTC will be working on an internet connection for the Raymond gym tomorrow. We will let you know when it is up and going. Hopefully by Wednesday.

We will begin compressing our serving times for lunch as well. Starting on Wednesday, we will serve from 11:00 AM until 12:30 PM. We do not have students showing up in that last half hour.

Have a great evening and we will provide an update again soon!

Jim Johnson
Superintendent

post_text:
KDHE is now recommending 14-day home quarantine for Kansans who have:
• Traveled to a state with known widespread community transmission (currently California, New
York and Washington state) on or after March 15.
• Visited Eagle, Summit, Pitkin and Gunnison counties in Colorado within the past week.
• Traveled on a cruise ship on or after March 15.
o People who have previously been told by Public Health to quarantine because of their cruise
ship travel should finish out their quarantine.
• Traveled internationally on or after March 15.
o People who have previously been told by Public Health to quarantine because of their
international travel should finish out their quarantine.
• Received notification from public health officials (state or local) that you are a close contact of a
laboratory-confirmed case of COVID-19. You should quarantine at home for 14 days since your
last contact with the case. (A close contact is defined as someone who has been closer than 6 feet
for more than 10 minutes while the patient is symptomatic.)

Are you planning to go watch Friday Night Lights in Stafford... Don't miss out on this tasty opportunity.

HOMECOMING HOG FEED

Come early to the Stafford Trojan Football game this Friday, September 27, 2019 and plan on enjoying some BBQ. The Junior Class Parents will be serving pulled pork sandwiches, cheesy potatoes, green beans, dessert, water or tea this Friday from 5:00 p.m. – 6:30 p.m. at the Stafford High School Shop which is located on the northeast corner of the high school. Each plate is $8.00 and all of the proceeds support the After Prom Party! The Junior Class Parents will also be supporting Taylor and Laeny Bauman with a donation jar which will be available during the BBQ for your donations to help cover medical and travel expenses during their stay in Wichita. So come early and don’t miss out!!!

post_text:
From the desk of Coach D

Thanks to everyone who came out for our Car Wash fundraiser tonight. The boys and I washed somewhere between 15-20 vehicles. The total amount of donations we received was very generous and will be used to buy drinks for road games, helmet decals, and general football expenditures. I am very proud of the work our boys put in tonight and we continue to bond as a team. Special thanks to Dawn Miller, who spearheaded the planning for the event and to the Chase Fire Department for letting us use their facilities and water. We were also able to help the Chase Food Bank as about 30-50 food items were donated. I'm excited to be welcomed by such a supportive community, Roll Kats!!!!#NovemberFootball.

post_text:
From the Desk of Coach D.

The scoreboard might not show it, but the 5-on-5 camp in Solomon was a success. The Chase Kats played three games against Solomon and Osborne, who were both runners-up in 8-man state championship games last season.
The Gorillas won Game 1 14-13 over the Kats. Osborne beat Chase 30-6 in Game 3 after shutting out Solomon in Game 2.
In Game 4 Chase lost 14-12 to Solomon.
The football program would like to thank the staff at Solomon for the invitation to participate in the event, and for hosting a quality camp.

The future looks bright. Roll Kats

post_text:
The 2019 Chase Football team will be traveling to Solomon, KS for a 5-on-5 Camp on Saturday. July 13.

5 teams are currently scheduled to attend the event, including 2018 State Champion runners-up Osborne, and Solomon. Also scheduled to attend are squads from Wilson and Peabody-Burns.

The first game is scheduled to begin at 10:00 a.m. Parents and attendees will not be charged an admission fee.

The Kats thank the Gorillas for the invitation and look forward to competing against such quality programs.
